          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #15\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#308\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:163`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:179`\n\nCustom detector kwargs are folded into a tuple for cache lookup. Passing a dict/list value causes `_DETECTOR_CACHE.get(cache_key)` to raise `TypeError` before the factory sees it.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Public extension API has a confusing failure mode.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Validate kwargs are hashable with a clear error, or recursively freeze common containers for cache keys.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-22T17:39:35Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Fixed in branch fix/security-review-batch-176-182. Added _assert_hashable_kwargs() helper that checks before cache key construction.",
