          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #15\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    Custom detector kwargs are folded into a cache tuple; unhashable values raise TypeError before the factory sees them.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    The public detector extension API has a confusing failure mode for dict/list configs.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:163`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:179`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Validate kwargs are hashable with a clear error, or recursively freeze common containers for cache keys.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:04:09Z",
